NAME		sched
SYNTAX		sched [-q] <delay> <command>
		sched [-q] @<time> <command>
DESCRIPTION	Schedules a command to execute in <delay> seconds or at a
		particular time, <time>. The <time> should be specified as
		hour:minute and is in 24 hour clock format.

		If the -q argument is not supplied, you will be shown the
		job id and event number as follows:
			[Job id] Event num

		The job can be terminated by issuing:
			kill <job id>
		or
			kill %<job id> (For unix junkies; me? never!)

SEE ALSO	kill, jobs, events
